21/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ruling Social Democrats suffered a major setback when they lost the mayoral election in the city of Cluj, polling agencies reported Sunday (20 June).
The party also lost four of Bucharest's five districts in what was seen as a major setback for Prime Minister Adrian Nastase.
His party's candidate for mayor of Bucharest, Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana, was defeated in the first round of voting.
Nastase said his government would stick to its current policies nonetheless.
(Rompres - 21/06/04;
AFP, Mediafax - 20/06/04)
